87
00:07:50,648 --> 00:07:54,889
So, so the viewing public so the useful thing to know is that.

88
00:07:55,610 --> 00:08:05,533
So in some places in some states in this country, and other places around the world, municipalities can define what's in their building code themselves.

89
00:08:06,113 --> 00:08:10,817
In Massachusetts, the municipalities have no control over the building code.

90
00:08:11,237 --> 00:08:12,738
It's a state building code.

91
00:08:13,319 --> 00:08:17,782
And we cannot make it any stricter than it is.

92
00:08:17,802 --> 00:08:25,028
And back in the early 2000s, people wanted a more advanced energy building code.

93
00:08:25,428 --> 00:08:34,015
So the way they did it was they said, here is a more advanced energy code that municipalities can choose to adopt if they want to.

94
00:08:34,579 --> 00:08:46,947
And so it basically meant rather than having, because there are 360 municipalities in our state, 360 building codes, there are two, the regular, the base building code and the stretch code.

95
00:08:48,248 --> 00:08:55,312
At this point, actually, it turns out that a very large majority of the municipalities have adopted the stretch code.

96
00:08:55,952 --> 00:09:03,357
And so they talked about, they basically made an advanced stretch code, which we were hoping would be this net zero code.

97
00:09:04,222 --> 00:09:05,263
It's not exactly.

98
00:09:06,563 --> 00:09:16,569
So now if communities want to be more progressive than everybody else, they can adopt this stricter building code, energy-wise.

99
00:09:16,589 --> 00:09:18,630
It's all with the energy.

100
00:09:18,730 --> 00:09:21,552
Which gives it that Monica stretch.

101
00:09:22,452 --> 00:09:22,812
Right.

102
00:09:22,932 --> 00:09:26,434
This is now an advanced version of the stretch.

103
00:09:26,454 --> 00:09:27,275
Over and above the...

104
00:09:28,143 --> 00:09:43,443
So it's a new opt in because every time the building code was updated by building professionals in internationally, Massachusetts would update a more advanced building code, and we, we kept stepping up in our stretch code kept stepping up.

105
00:09:44,370 --> 00:09:49,153
Um, so now there's this new version that's an opt in again.

106
00:09:49,734 --> 00:09:51,875
And so, anybody who wants to partake in it.

